x4freetext: High purity Zr (99.98%) from Goodfellow with thickness
technique was used. Stacks consisted of Zr target, Ti
and Al monitor, Al energy degrader and other target
foils. The stacks were irradiated in a Faraday-cup
like target holder. Irradiations took place at beam
current of 160 nA for 60 min (VUB) and 24 nA for 30
used. Activity level of the target foils were
followed. Energy loss of the proton beam was
calculated by polynomial approximation of Andersen
and Ziegler (1977) or calculated with the help of the
SRIM code (Ziegler, 2013). Decay data were taken from
